How to Set Up PNETLab and Import Images

1. Download and install VMware Workstation or VMware Player.

2. Download the PNETLab .ova file from:
   https://pnetlab.com/pages/download

3. Launch VMware and allow any required permissions.

4. Go to:
   File > Open

5. Select the downloaded PNETLab .ova file.
   Recommended VM requirements:
   - 8 GB RAM
   - 4 CPU cores
   - 100 GB disk space

6. Ensure virtualization is enabled in your BIOS settings,
   otherwise the OVA will not boot.

7. Once the import is complete, power on the virtual machine.

8. Note the IP address displayed in the VM CLI and access it from your browser.

9. Log in to the PNETLab portal using either online or offline mode.
   (Refer to their official website for details.)

10. After logging in to the web GUI, click on "Add a Lab".

11. Install WinSCP and connect to your PNETLab VM using its IP address.

12. Use the default credentials:
    Username: root
    Password: pnet

13. Navigate to the directory:
    /opt/unetlab/addons

14. Based on the image type (qemu, iou, or dynamips),
    copy and paste the entire image folder into the respective directory.
    Do not rename the folder.

15. Example:
    A folder named "asav-984-10" should be placed inside the qemu directory.

16. After copying the folder, check its permissions.
    Ensure they are set to: rwxr-xr-x
    (You can verify and modify permissions manually if required.)

17. Refresh the PNETLab web GUI.
    The imported image should now appear as an available node.

18. Click on "Add Node", select Cisco ASA,
    choose the required number of interfaces, and you're ready to start.

